main event: Naval message describing sightings of unidentified objects with bright blue-green lights, high altitude, and high speed.
interesting points: Approximately 30 objects were identified, with the main observation being 15 of them., Objects were reported to have a bright blue-green light and were estimated to be at altitudes of 30,000 to 60,000 feet., The objects were sighted moving at an estimated speed of 2,000 knots., Sightings occurred at regular intervals and were communicated via a naval message., The sightings are part of records from Project Blue Book relating to unidentified aerial phenomena.
sighted object: Unidentified objects with bright blue-green lights
witness description: Naval and Air Force personnel involved in monitoring airborne objects
